Yes exactly! But let me give you the full picture with the catch:

How It Works
You update the Excel file daily
          ↓
Save it to Shared Network Folder
(\\192.168.1.XX\Dashboards)
          ↓
Team opens file from that same folder
          ↓
They see your dashboard with slicers & charts ✅
The One Big Catch — Simultaneous Editing
Situation	What Happens
One person opens at a time	✅ Works perfectly
Multiple people open together	⚠️ Excel locks the file
Someone else is editing	❌ Others get "Read Only" mode
The Fix — Mark it Read Only for Team
Since your team only needs to view and filter (not edit), do this:

File → Info → Protect Workbook → Mark as Final

Or simpler — just tell them:

"When Excel asks 'Open as Read Only?' — click Yes"

This way everyone can open simultaneously with no conflicts, and your slicers/filters still work for each person individually.

What Your Team Experience Looks Like
Team member opens shared folder in File Explorer
          ↓
Double clicks Dashboard.xlsm
          ↓
Clicks "Enable Macros" (one time warning)
          ↓
Sees your full dashboard with slicers & charts
Filters by model, date, whatever you built
          ↓
They CANNOT accidentally edit or break anything ✅
The Only Remaining Question
Do you have a shared network folder already?

If yes → you're basically ready to go today
If no → ask your IT or manager: "Can I get a shared folder on the LAN for my team?" — this is a very standard, zero-risk request they will likely approve immediately
That's genuinely it. No server, no Python, no Power BI — just a shared folder and your Excel file.

